            </text>
            <standOff>
                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="typednotes">
                    
                    	<note xml:id="n_transcrSource" type="transcrSource">
                    	    
<p>Original manuscript</p>
                    	</note>
                    
                    
                    	<note xml:id="n_dating" type="dating">
                    	    
<p>Van Gogh is still waiting for Van Rappard’s reply to <ref target="let517.xml">letter 517</ref>, and says ‘once more’ that unpleasant as he finds the disagreement which has arisen, he is nonetheless willing to regard it as a ‘misunderstanding’ <ref target="#l-8">(l. 8)</ref> which it must be possible to put right. He now urges him to come to a decision about their friendship, which has to be taken ‘this week’ <ref target="#l-13">(l. 13)</ref>. From the next letter to Van Rappard, which was written on 27 July, it appears that Van Gogh wants to patch up the quarrel – this must have been in response to Van Rappard’s reply. We have therefore dated the letter between about Tuesday, 21 and Friday, 24 July 1885. Cf. <ref target="let522.xml">letter 522</ref>, <hi rend="italics">Date</hi>.</p>
                    	</note>
                    
                    
                    
